** Procedure For Optimization - Diagnosing And Servicing Each Unit **
You Will Be Required To Take Specific Temperature Readings With Your Fluke Or Similar Temperature Probes Clamp On Sensors Work Best For Liquid Line Temp Readings 1. Perform A Physical Inspection Of Equipment And Note Any Issues 2. Fill Out Y/N Equipment Condition Questions And Take Required Photographs 3. Make Sure That The Unit Is Running 100% Cooling Or Heating Before Taking Temp Readings. 4. Record Measurements As Specified **Before** Any Repairs Are Made 5. Submit/Upload The Diagnostic Form 6. Receive Diagnostic Email - Check Your Email Shortly After Uploading The Survey Form 7. Determine What Repairs Are Needed 8. Repair Equipment Or Submit A Quote For Repairs When Nte Would Be Exceeded 9. After Repairs Are Made Use The Serviceqc Survey Form To Verify That The Units Are Fully Optimzed And Performing Correctly See Hyperlink Below To Identify The Specific Locations For Taking Each Temp Reading
